text.section:
A lender may not take as security for a loan any:
Confession of judgment or power of attorney to him or to a third person to confess judgment or appear for the borrower in a judicial proceeding;
Assignment or order for payment of wages;
Instrument in which blanks are left to be filled after execution; or
Note, promise to pay, or security instrument which does not state:
The principal amount of the loan;
A schedule of payments or a description of the schedule; and
The agreed amount and rate of interest, charges, and fees.

section.section:
Acceptable third-party written documentation includes:
The borrower's Internal Revenue Service form W-2;
A copy of the borrower's income tax return;
Payroll receipts;
The records of a financial institution; or
Other third-party documents that provide reasonably reliable evidence of the borrower's income or assets.
